9.Sort descending.

imp-->
Ascending Bubble Sort: if l[j] > l[j + 1]
Descending Bubble Sort: if l[j] < l[j + 1]

1st approach-->
l = [4, 8, 9, 2, 5, 1] #9,8,5,4,2,1

l.sort(reverse=True)
print(l)
TC: O(n log n)
SC: O(n)



2nd approach-->
l = [4, 8, 9, 2, 5, 1] #9,8,5,4,2,1

desc=sorted(l,reverse=True)
print(desc)
TC: O(n log n)
SC: O(n)
